Nigeria National League side, Crown Football Club of Ogbomosho will return to the Soun Stadium for their home matches this season. General Manager of the Ajilete Warriors Kunle Oyeleye disclosed this in a chat with DAILY POST. Oyeleye, whose side have adopted the Ladoke Akintola University Stadium as their home ground for the past two seasons, stated that the stadium is eighty percent completed and will be ready for the new season. “We will be playing our home matches at the Soun Stadium this season,” Oyeleye stated. “Though we have recorded tremendous success at LAUTECH Stadium but no place compares to our home ground. “The playing turf is 80% completed with our dressing room too almost completed as well.” The 2023 NNL season will start on March 3.